/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"score\": 0.9999999999988631, \"rank\": 5.94749940270404e-13, \"text\": \"American woman\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q2188189\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Woman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch all the action from the Paris Olympic and Paralympic Games live on Peacock  The Washington, D.C., native won four total medals in Paris: gold in the women's 1500m freestyle and 800m freestyle, silver in the 4x200m freestyle relay and bronze in the 400m freestyle.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 847, \"end\": 852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999993805659, \"rank\": 6.1942866867354875e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Union_Station\", \"score\": 0.945700376631678, \"rank\": 0.0489424951782253, \"text\": \"Washington, D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Union_Station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Washington_Union_Station\"}, {\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999993805659, \"rank\": 6.1942866867354875e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She set an Olympic record in the 1500m win, posting a time of 15:30.02.\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With 14 total Olympic medals, Ledecky is the fifth-most decorated athlete in the history of the competition.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Torri Huske left the T