100m freestyle and 4x100m freestyle relay.\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Additionally, she helped set a new world record in both the women's 4x100m medley relay and the mixed 4x100m medley relay.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1732, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7624628493894214e-23, \"text\": \"4x100m medley relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. women swimmers dominated when it came to earning golds and other medals.\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1865, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's side was led by 24-year-old Bobby Finke.\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1904, \"end\": 1915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bobby Finke\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Finke\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finke, who won two golds in Tokyo in the 800m and 1500m freestyles, had similar performances in Paris.\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9825053680413182, \"rank\": 0.017806143892605965, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2014, \"end\": 2019, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999993805659, \"rank\": 6.1942866867354875e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Tampa, Fla., native repeated as the gold medalist in the 1500m, setting a world record in the process at 14:30.67.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He also won silver in the 800m, losing out to Ireland's Daniel Wiffen, who set an Olympic record in the event.\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2188, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.7303646816106731, \"rank\": 0.3483219403943301, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not always seem like it at first, but the U.S. turned things around in the final stretches to seize the head-to-head advantage over Australia in theirheated swimming rivalry.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2393, \"end\": 2402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.998923133362586, \"rank\": 0.0008272700989635133, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. won in terms of both total medals (28 to 18) and, more narrowly, most golds (eight to seven).\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australian rising star Ariarne Titmus, 23, added four more medals to her name after winning four in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 2541, \"to\": 2647, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2541, \"end\": 2551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9759345430525979, \"rank\": 0.02463480799117719, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2564, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 2641, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9825053680413182, \"rank\": 0.017806143892605965, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those included two golds and two silvers.\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2689, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kaylee McKeown, also 23 and won four medals in Tokyo, earned five in Paris.\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2691, \"end\": 2705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaylee McKeown\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kaylee_McKeown\"}, {\"begin\": 2738, \"end\": 2743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9825053680413182, \"rank\": 0.017806143892605965, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 2760, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999993805659, \"rank\": 6.1942866867354875e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She collected two golds, one silver and two bronzes as one of Australia's best performers.\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2829, \"end\": 2838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.998923133362586, \"rank\": 0.0008272700989635133, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In terms of most gold medals, France, thanks to rising star Leon Marchand, won four to be right behind the U.S. and Australia in that category.\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 3002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2889, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9924391915951227, \"rank\": 0.004729697412388532, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.999997690734455, \"rank\": 1.6843225896973646e-06, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}, {\"begin\": 2975, \"end\": 2984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.998923133362586, \"rank\": 0.0008272700989635133, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in terms of most in total, China was actually in the third spot.\", \"from\": 3004, \"to\": 3072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3035, \"end\": 3040, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6022810191284388, \"rank\": 0.5501287353061165, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China claimed 12 swimming medals thanks to seven of them being bronze.\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3143, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3073, \"end\": 3078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6022810191284388, \"rank\": 0.5501287353061165, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pan Zhanle won the only individual gold -- the other was the men's 4x100m medley relay team -- while Zhang Yufei won bronze in three individual women's events.\", \"from\": 3145, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3212, \"end\": 3231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7624628493894214e-23, \"text\": \"4x100m medley relay\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3246, \"end\": 3257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\", \"score\": 0.9727864122994488, \"rank\": 0.027972027972030022, \"text\": \"Zhang Yufei\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Yufei_(swimmer)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tired of the fours?Leon Marchandwasn't.\", \"from\": 3306, \"to\": 3345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old French swimmer had an Olympic campaign to remember in front of his home crowd.\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3363, \"end\": 3369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7097137953059786, \"rank\": 0.22475469625548064, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He won all four of his individual events: the 200m breaststroke, 200m butterfly, 200m individual medley and 400m individual medley.\", \"from\": 3442, \"to\": 3573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he won the 400m individual medley, he brought home France's first swimming medal since 2012.\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3672, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3631, \"end\": 3637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9924391915951227, \"rank\": 0.004729697412388532, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also became the fourth swimmer to win two individual golds on the same day, which was last accomplished in 1976.\", \"from\": 3674, \"to\": 3789, \"entities\": []}]}"